The course provides an overview of the technologies used to ensure the quality of the environment. Particular attention will be paid to ensuring safety requirements in the work environment, reduction of risk factors, and technological developments in this field. The economic aspects of environmental technology are also addressed.

Geology and Environmental Technology 1st year students are recommended to register in the autumn semester in addition to this compulsory subject but also the introductory applied subject LOOM.00.031 "Applications of Geology and Environmental Technology".Objectives/eesmärkid:  To introduce students to the different fields of environmental technology. To give an overview of the basic principles of the processes taking place in the environment and the related technological solutions. The subject provides an introductory overview of the field of environmental technology, introduces general concepts, structure and terminology. The subject develops students' career planning skills.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course student: - knows the various natural processes and/or the results of human activities using environmental technological solutions - has an overview of different energy sources and is able to compare them with each other - knows the directions of specialization in environmental technology at the University of Tartu - has an overview of different career opportunities in the field of environmental technology - has an idea of the history and current state of environmental technology - has an overview of the basic concepts and theoretical principles of the field of geology - is familiar with current problems in the field of environmental technology - analyses and targets their professional study and studies and career choices
